## Chimera removal

Chimeric sequences are artificial sequences that can arise during PCR amplification when two or more parental sequences are combined. These artifacts can lead to false positive taxa and inflated diversity estimates in microbial community analyses.

To ensure data quality, chimera removal was performed on cleaned 16S sequences in FASTA format (.fa.gz) using VSEARCH v2.30.0 with the --uchime_denovo algorithm. This method detects chimeras de novo based on sequence abundance and k-mer patterns, without requiring a reference database.

### Install VSEARCH

`conda create -n vsearch_env -c bioconda -c conda-forge vsearch`
`conda activate vsearch_env`
`vsearch --version`

